originalText.text:
Jupiter in Rockefeller Center has been a regular place for us, but I've yet to give it a proper review. Tonight, we were again recognized as regular customers and treated to zucchini fritters‚Äîcrispy and perfectly seasoned.
I stuck to my usual glass of blanc de blanc to start, while my partner tried the bianco negroni, which he loved. Our must have Nebbiolo bottle was again a standout, offering great quality without being too pricey.
For starters, I had the carpaccio, nicely balanced with watercress and mustard. My partner had the pasta cacio e pepe that was even better than last time.
Moving on to mains, my Bisteca was spot-on, and the Pesce alla Griglia (red snapper) was outstanding.
Dessert was tiramisu for two, though we could've gone for another because it was so delicious.
We finished off with some recommended Amaro from the friendly staff.
The mix of after-work locals, tourists, and even film crews from local network studios made for a lively atmosphere.
In short, Jupiter offers consistent quality and a welcoming vibe that keeps us coming back.

originalText.text: We dined at this restaurant last week and had a fantastic experience, so we decided to bring our kids for dinner. To start, we enjoyed a selection of appetizers, including crudo, fried zucchini, calamari, and bread. For the main course, we enjoyed flavorful spaghetti with tender pork and veal meatballs, pappardelli, as well as the delightful grilled snapper with artichoke in a light salsa base, and the amazing sirloin with potatoes. To top off the meal, we indulged in a variety of desserts, including montebianco, tiramisu, chocolate, and vanilla ice cream, and a personal favorite of mine, ricotta cheese sorbet. The restaurant also offered an excellent selection of wines and dessert wines. It was a wonderful Christmas dinner with family, and it made it even more special when our kids picked up the tab üéÖüëç

originalText.text: I really liked this place. They open up the doors so you can see the rink at Rockefeller. The interior design is gorgeous, open concept so you can see them cook your food which is entertaining. I liked all the food we got. The scallops for the main were incredibly good and light, I always appreciate leaving not overly full. Their blanco negroni wasn‚Äôt my favourite, its refreshing but I prefer it to have more flavour. Be sure to get the burrata, that with the red peppers was a great combo.

originalText.text: Service was great and food was good but the vibe/ambiance was underwhelming - a strange mix of corporate and touristy. I realize I didn't take photos of our pasta mains - I had the vongole. The desserts were the highlight especially the Cassata Fredda which is a ricotta-type ice cream with candied orange and dark chocolate. That I might come back for.....

originalText.text: A lovely relaxing place to have my birthday dinner! On a weekday evening was quiet even with the business diners around us. Service was excellent, attentive and accommodating. We took our time to enjoy cocktails and appetizers- the endive salad, which was excellent and also fresh mozzarella which was ok. The wines were decent and broad selection to pair with the several fresh pastas or dinners, we had the spaghetti, which was ok and the veal lasagna, excellent. Save room for the tiramusu!! Prices are high, esp with the portion size, suppose it is to be expected given the prime location in NYC but also the atmosphere and service. Enjoy!
